    "body": "\"Warning about windows\", so sad that Windows' character is being assasinated by GitBash/mintty :(\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, GitBash/mintty are giving windows a bad rep here by looking like a terminal to a user, but telling the applications they spawn that they're not a terminal: https://github.com/git-for-windows/git/wiki/FAQ#some-native-console-programs-dont-work-when-run-from-git-bash-how-to-fix-it\r\n\r\nIf you wanted to include an error message for GitBash specifically, it /could/ include one of the following workarounds:\r\n\r\n`winpty bash \"$(which npx)\" hardhat`\r\n`winpty bash \"$(which npx)\" hardhat init`\r\n\r\nWhich restore hardhat functionality with no patches.\r\n\r\nIt might be beneficial to direct the users to here: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/dev-environment/javascript/nodejs-on-wsl which is the microsoft doc recommending the use of WSL for node-dev, or to have a page in the HH docs explaining that GitBash isn't a terminal, and why users should avoid it - but that's really straying from HH and documenting other projects in your docs, which I appreciate you may not want to do.",
